INSERT INTO `instructions` VALUES (1,'Fill a large pot with about 4-6 quarts of water. Place the pot on the stove over high heat and cover it with a lid. Allow the water to come to a rolling boil. This will serve as the base for cooking your pasta.',1,1),(2,'Once the water is vigorously boiling, add a tablespoon of salt. Stir the salt into the boiling water to ensure even distribution. Adding salt enhances the flavor of the pasta as it absorbs the seasoned water during cooking.',2,1),(3,'Gently add the spaghetti to the boiling water. Use a stirring spoon to ensure the pasta doesn’t stick together. Cook the spaghetti according to the package instructions or until it reaches the desired level of doneness. Remember, al dente pasta has a slight firmness when bitten.',3,1),(4,'Carefully drain the cooked spaghetti in a colander in the sink. Shake the colander to remove excess water. Optionally, you can save a cup of the pasta water, as it may come in handy later for adjusting the sauce consistency. Set the drained spaghetti aside for use in the final steps of your delicious spaghetti dish.',4,1),(5,'Chop a variety of fresh vegetables such as bell peppers, broccoli, carrots, and snap peas. Prep the vegetables and set them aside for stir-frying.',1,2),(6,'Heat a wok or large pan over medium-high heat. Add a tablespoon of vegetable oil and let it heat up. Swirl the oil to coat the bottom of the pan evenly.',2,2),(7,'Add minced garlic and ginger to the hot oil. Sauté for about 30 seconds until fragrant, being careful not to burn the garlic.',3,2),(8,'Add the prepared vegetables to the pan. Stir-fry them quickly, ensuring they are cooked but still crisp. You can add soy sauce or other seasonings for flavor.',4,2),(9,'Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add fettuccine pasta and cook according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside.',1,3),(10,'Season chicken breasts with salt, pepper, and any desired herbs. In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through. Remove from the skillet and set aside.',2,3),(11,'In the same skillet, melt butter and add minced garlic. Sauté until fragrant. Pour in heavy cream and bring to a simmer.',3,3),(12,'Stir in grated Parmesan cheese and continue to cook, stirring constantly, until the sauce thickens. Season with salt and pepper to taste.',4,3),(13,'Rinse quinoa thoroughly under cold water. In a medium saucepan, combine quinoa and water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes or until quinoa is cooked and water is absorbed.',1,4),(14,'While quinoa is cooking, chop and prepare fresh vegetables such as cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, and bell peppers. Mix them in a large salad bowl.',2,4),(15,'In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, salt, and pepper to create the dressing.',3,4),(16,'Once quinoa is cooked and slightly cooled, add it to the salad bowl with the fresh vegetables. Pour the dressing over the salad and toss everything together until well combined.',4,4),(17,'In a skillet over medium-high heat, brown ground beef. Season with taco seasoning and cook until fully browned. Drain excess fat if necessary.',1,5),(18,'While the beef is cooking, chop fresh toppings such as lettuce, tomatoes, onions, and cilantro. Grate cheese and set aside.',2,5),(19,'Warm taco shells in the oven or on the stovetop according to the package instructions. Assemble the tacos by spooning the seasoned beef into the shells.',3,5),(20,'Top the tacos with your favorite toppings, including shredded cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, onions, and a sprinkle of fresh cilantro. Add salsa, sour cream, or guacamole if desired.',4,5),(21,'In a large pot, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add diced onions, carrots, and celery. Sauté until the vegetables are softened and the onions are translucent.',1,6),(22,'Add minced garlic to the pot and sauté for an additional minute until fragrant. Season with salt, pepper, and any desired herbs or spices.',2,6),(23,'Pour in vegetable or chicken broth, and add diced potatoes and any other vegetables you prefer such as zucchini, bell peppers, or tomatoes. Bring the soup to a simmer.',3,6),(24,'Simmer the soup for about 20-25 minutes or until the vegetables are tender. Taste and adjust the seasoning if necessary. Serve hot and enjoy your comforting vegetable soup!',4,6),(25,'Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C). Place salmon fillets on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.',1,7),(26,'In a small bowl, mix together teriyaki sauce, soy sauce, honey, minced garlic, and grated ginger to create the teriyaki marinade.',2,7),(27,'Brush the teriyaki marinade over the salmon fillets, ensuring they are evenly coated. Let the salmon marinate for about 15-20 minutes to absorb the flavors.',3,7),(28,'Bake the salmon in the preheated oven for 15-20 minutes or until the salmon flakes easily with a fork. Optionally, broil for a couple of minutes for a caramelized finish.',4,7),(29,'Start by marinating the pork in a mixture of soy sauce, garlic, honey, and your preferred herbs and spices. Allow it to marinate in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours or overnight for more flavor.',1,10),(30,'Preheat your grill to medium-high heat. Remove the pork from the marinade and let any excess drip off. Grill the pork for about 15-20 minutes, turning occasionally, until it reaches the desired level of doneness.',2,10),(31,'While the pork is grilling, you can baste it with the remaining marinade to add extra flavor. Make sure to cook the pork thoroughly, reaching a safe internal temperature.',3,10),(32,'Once grilled to perfection, let the pork rest for a few minutes before slicing. Serve the grilled pork with your favorite sides and enjoy!',4,10),(33,'Start by cooking jasmine rice according to package instructions. It is ideal to use day-old rice for fried rice as it tends to be drier and less sticky.',1,11),(34,'In a large wok or skillet, heat sesame oil over medium-high heat. Add diced carrots, peas, and corn. Sauté the vegetables until they are tender-crisp.',2,11),(35,'Push the vegetables to the side of the wok and crack eggs into the empty space. Scramble the eggs until they are just set, and then mix them with the sautéed vegetables.',3,11),(36,'Add the cooked rice to the wok. Pour in soy sauce and stir-fry the rice and vegetables together until everything is well combined and heated through.',4,11),(37,'Preheat the grill or stovetop pan over medium-high heat. If using a grill, make sure to oil the grates to prevent sticking.',1,12),(38,'In a mixing bowl, combine ground beef with salt, pepper, and any desired seasonings. Divide the mixture into equal portions and shape them into burger patties.',2,12),(39,'Place the burger patties on the preheated grill or pan. Cook for about 4-5 minutes per side for medium doneness, or adjust the cooking time according to your preference.',3,12),(40,'Optional: Add cheese slices on top of the burgers during the last minute of cooking to melt the cheese. Toast burger buns on the grill for a minute until golden brown.',4,12),(41,'Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Cook linguine pasta according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside.',1,13),(42,'In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add minced garlic and red pepper flakes. Sauté until the garlic is golden but not browned.',2,13),(43,'Add shrimp to the skillet and cook until they turn pink and opaque. Stir in white wine, lemon juice, and chopped parsley. Simmer for a few minutes.',3,13),(44,'Toss the cooked linguine with the shrimp and sauce. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Serve the Shrimp Scampi hot, garnished with additional parsley and grated Parmesan cheese.',4,13),(45,'Start by cooking jasmine rice according to package instructions. It is recommended to use day-old rice for fried rice for better texture.',1,14),(46,'In a wok or large skillet, heat vegetable oil over medium-high heat. Add diced pork and cook until browned and cooked through.',2,14),(47,'Push the pork to the side and add beaten eggs to the empty space. Scramble the eggs until just set, and then mix them with the cooked pork.',3,14),(48,'Add the cooked rice to the wok. Pour in soy sauce and stir-fry the rice, pork, and eggs together until well combined. Optionally, add diced vegetables like peas and carrots.',4,14),(49,'In a mixing bowl, combine fresh strawberries, sugar, and a splash of lemon juice. Toss the strawberries to coat them evenly and let them sit for about 15 minutes.',1,15),(50,'In serving glasses or bowls, layer the macerated strawberries with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.',2,15),(51,'Top the dessert with additional strawberries and a drizzle of chocolate or strawberry sauce, if desired. Serve immediately and enjoy your refreshing Strawberry Dessert!',3,15),(52,'Preheat the oven to 450°F (230°C). Roll out pizza dough on a floured surface and transfer it to a pizza stone or baking sheet.',1,16),(53,'Spread pizza sauce evenly over the dough. Top with shredded mozzarella cheese and a variety of fresh vegetables such as bell peppers, tomatoes, olives, and onions.',2,16),(54,'Bake the pizza in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes or until the crust is golden and the cheese is melted and bubbly.',3,16),(55,'Remove the pizza from the oven, let it cool slightly, and then slice. Serve the Vegetable Pizza hot and enjoy!',4,16),(56,'Lay out a tortilla on a flat surface. Spread a thin layer of mayonnaise or your favorite sauce over the tortilla.',1,17),(57,'Layer sliced turkey, lettuce, tomatoes, and any other desired toppings (such as cheese, avocado, or bacon) on the tortilla.',2,17),(58,'Fold in the sides of the tortilla and then roll it up tightly from the bottom to create a wrap. Secure the wrap with toothpicks if needed.',3,17),(59,'Slice the Turkey Wrap in half diagonally and serve. Enjoy a quick and delicious turkey wrap!',4,17),(60,'Fill a 