. Add peeled and deveined prawns to the skillet.',1,23),(80,'Season the prawns with salt, pepper, and a pinch of paprika. Cook until the prawns are pink and cooked through.',2,23),(81,'Add minced garlic, chopped tomatoes, and fresh basil to the skillet. Sauté for a few minutes until the tomatoes are softened and the flavors meld together.',3,23),(82,'Serve the Prawn Paradise over cooked pasta or rice. Garnish with additional basil and a squeeze of lemon if desired.',4,23),(83,'Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C). Season fish fillets with salt, pepper, and any desired herbs or spices.',1,25),(84,'Place the seasoned fish fillets on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Drizzle with olive oil and bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes or until the fish flakes easily.',2,25),(85,'While the fish is baking, prepare a salsa by combining diced tomatoes, red onion, cilantro, lime juice, and salt.',3,25),(86,'Serve the Fish Fiesta by topping the baked fish with the fresh salsa. Enjoy a flavorful and light fish dish!',4,25),(87,'In a large mixing bowl, combine diced chicken with hot sauce, garlic powder, onion powder, and paprika. Let it marinate for at least 30 minutes.',1,26),(88,'In a skillet over medium-high heat, cook the marinated chicken until browned and cooked through. Add additional hot sauce for extra spice if desired.',2,26),(89,'Layer tortilla chips on a serving platter. Spoon the spicy chicken over the chips. Sprinkle shredded cheese over the top.',3,26),(90,'Optional: Garnish with sliced jalapeños, diced tomatoes, and chopped green onions. Serve the Spicy Delight nachos immediately.',4,26),(91,'Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C). In a mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, and any desired herbs or spices.',1,28),(92,'Add melted butter and milk to the dry ingredients. Stir until just combined. Optionally, fold in grated cheese or chopped herbs for added flavor.',2,28),(93,'Drop spoonfuls of the dough onto a baking sheet. Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes or until the tops are golden brown.',3,28),(94,'Serve the Bread Bonanza biscuits warm. Enjoy them as a side for soups, stews, or any meal of your choice.',4,28),(95,'In a large bowl, combine a variety of fresh fruits such as strawberries, blueberries, grapes, and kiwi.',1,30),(96,'In a small bowl, whisk together honey and lemon juice. Drizzle the honey-lemon mixture over the fresh fruits and gently toss to coat.',2,30),(97,'Optional: Garnish with mint leaves for a burst of freshness. Serve the Fruit Bliss salad chilled and enjoy a refreshing and healthy dessert.',3,30);
